sentences: Max Surban (born Maximo Surban, May 15, 1939) is a Filipino singer in mainly in Cebuano language.
They were also in the Pamilya Ukay-OKay comedy TV show in Cebu.
He also composed songs for Pilita Corrales includes their duets such as Kon Magkabulag Ta, Gugmang Dinali-Dali, Pagbantay Gyud Inday and Diyos Ko Day songs.
In 2019, Surban was recognized as one of the Top 100 Cebuano personalities by The Freeman, Cebu's longest-running newspaper.
